request.description:
**The Fix: `List` → `Set` on `@OneToMany`**

Change your entity collections from `List` to `Set`:

```java
// ❌ BEFORE — bag, causes MultipleBagFetchException
@OneToMany(mappedBy = "user")
private List<Post> posts = new ArrayList<>();

// ✅ AFTER — set, safe to JOIN FETCH simultaneously
@OneToMany(mappedBy = "user")
private Set<Post> posts = new LinkedHashSet<>();
```

With `Set`, Hibernate can safely deduplicate the Cartesian product rows, allowing `@EntityGraph` to fetch multiple nested collections in a **single query**.

**Returns HTTP 200** — 3 users with posts and images all loaded in 1 query.
